{
  "text": "14 While the local pH was not recorded, we assumed the local pH near the cathode could range from the bulk solution pH 8.0 to as high as 12.0. Such a high local pH was recorded in a biofilm by using a micro pH sensor. [CITATION_1] Based on the wastewater composition (Table S1 ), at least 16 precipitates including calcium phosphate, magnesium precipitates, and carbonate precipitates may form and precipitate from the wastewater in response to high local pH, as indicated by the SI of these",
